vity ranged from 25.6% to 113% for Jaszczak spheres ranging in\nvolume from 0.5 ml to 16 ml.\n  Conclusion: The accuracy of Monte Carlo-based dosimetry for Iodine-131 RPT in\nhead and neck cancer was validated with an anthropomorphic phantom. Future\napplications of the phantom could involve 3D printing and characterizing\npatient specific volumes for more personalized RPT dosimetry estimates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Feb 2022 21:11:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-10"}
